photos.Locality: Coyote Point County Park--harbor and marsh
photos.Observation Details: Immature bird best views - in front of yacht club building - I hope Derek posts the The pictures  of this desert sparrow bathing. I did not realize these guys were so tiny until I saw this bird side by side with a junco and white throated sparrow - maybe 2/3 the size...  Supposed resident desert bird but I think desert birds disperse as they are alwAys dealing with droughts and that explains what this bird is in San Mateo - a young bird off course as pRt of a desert related natural dispersal.

Spotted just as I was getting into my car in back of small bush near entrance to community garden. Thought it was Yellow-rumped but tail pumping got me to stop and quickly realize it was a Palm Warbler with yellow vent, etc.  Bob Gunderson drove up right at that time so I got him on it and David Assman and a few other folks soon were on it before I had to leave for my next stop
